'''Francisco Ruiz Velasco''' is a [[Wikipedia:Mexicans|Mexican]] artist who drew for various [[Star Wars comic books|''Star Wars'' comics]] published by [[Dark Horse Comics|Dark Horse]].

Born in [[Wikipedia:Mexico|Mexico]] in [[1972]], he spent many afternoons of his childhood immersed in [[Wikipedia:Anime|anime]] from the 1970s and 1980s.<ref name="Cara" /> He has also drawn for [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] and [[Wikipedia:DC Comics|DC]],<ref name="Artstation" /> and in [[2001]] he was nominated for [[Wikipedia:Russ Manning Most Promising Newcomer Award|Most Promising Newcomer]] at the [[Wikipedia:Eisner Awards|Eisner Awards]].<ref name="Humanoids">{{WebCite|url=https://www.humanoids.com/author/4024|title=Ruiz Velasco|work=Humanoids|archivedate=20240421105030}}</ref>

Velasco has worked in the art department as a concept designer for such movies as ''[[Wikipedia:Pacific Rim (film)|Pacific Rim]]'' and ''[[Wikipedia:Thor: Ragnarok|Thor: Ragnarok]]''. He directed the short film ''A Gentlemen's Duel''.<ref name="Artstation" />
